+{"id":"frankenpandas-rb1gy","title":"fd90.170: README select_dtypes(strs) wrong — needs select_dtypes_by_name for &str args","description":"fd90.74-169 follow-on. Line 1530 in Selection and Indexing shows:

  let numeric = df.select_dtypes(&["int64", "float64"], &[])?;

But crates/fp-frame/src/lib.rs has TWO variants:
  line 25920: pub fn select_dtypes(&self, include: &[DType], exclude: &[DType])
  line 25950: pub fn select_dtypes_by_name(&self, include: &[&str], exclude: &[&str])

The string-name variant is select_dtypes_by_name. The plain select_dtypes takes &[DType] enum values. Note that line 1119 in Advanced Selection Methods correctly uses the DType variant:
  df.select_dtypes(&[DType::Int64, DType::Float64], &[])?

So Selection and Indexing at line 1530 was already inconsistent with the existing correct example — likely written first then the API split.

Fix: switch line 1530 to select_dtypes_by_name to match the &str literals shown, or change the args to &[DType::Int64, DType::Float64]. Going with the by_name variant since the README is showing the user-friendly string aliases.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-26T16:45:19.411978137Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T16:46:49.797386210Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T16:46:49.794613947Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
